        content:
          "When you buy tires, the purchase price is only part of the total cost. Installation involves several distinct services that some shops bundle and others charge separately, making it difficult to compare total costs between tire retailers. Understanding each component helps you evaluate whether you are getting a fair deal. Mounting is the process of removing the old tire from the wheel and installing the new tire. This requires a tire machine that breaks the bead seal on the old tire, pulls it off the wheel, stretches the new tire over the rim, and inflates it to seat the bead. The mounting process takes about 10 to 15 minutes per tire for a standard passenger wheel and tire combination. Low-profile tires and large or specialty wheels require more care and time to avoid damage. Some shops charge $15 to $25 per tire for mounting alone. Balancing is the process of spinning the mounted tire and wheel assembly on a computerized balancer to identify heavy spots, then attaching small weights to the wheel to compensate. An unbalanced tire creates a vibration felt through the steering wheel or seat, and it causes uneven tire wear. Balancing takes about 10 minutes per tire. Some shops charge $10 to $20 per tire for balancing. Valve stem replacement involves removing the old rubber valve stem — or the rubber gasket on TPMS-equipped metal valve stems — and installing a new one. Old valve stems can crack and leak, causing slow air loss. Rubber valve stems cost $2 to $5 each. TPMS service involves resetting or reprogramming the tire pressure monitoring system sensors after the tires are installed. This ensures the system reads correctly and the TPMS warning light does not illuminate. TPMS reset takes five to 15 minutes depending on the vehicle and may require a dedicated TPMS programming tool. Some shops charge $5 to $15 per wheel for TPMS service. Old tire disposal involves properly disposing of the removed tires, which cannot go in regular trash. Tire disposal fees are typically $3 to $5 per tire.",
